      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Otisville,_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Erie Railroad’s arrival in 1846 turned Otisville into a regional commerce and transportation hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Otisville,_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A 1906 sanitarium near the village later became a New York state prison, reflecting a shift from health to correctional use.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
